The paper focuses on developing a hybrid system for a humanoid robot to perform indoor tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The system combines SLAM algorithm with object recognition, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The object recognition technique used in the system is based on SIFT and RANSAC, which are popular machine learning algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the system aims to make the robot more autonomous, which involves control and system engineering (cs.SY).
